Margot-Robbie-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Ryan-Gosling-and-Margot-Robbie-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Ryan-Gosling-and-Margot-Robbie-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p><a href="https://www.nme.com/tag/barbie"><em>芭比</em></a>明星<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/margot-robbie">玛格特·罗比</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/ryan-gosling">瑞恩·高斯林</a>将在一部新电影中重聚。</p><ul class="post-content-read-more"><li><strong>阅读更多：<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/barbie-review-margot-robbie-ryan-gosling-3470019">《芭比娃娃》评论：格蕾塔·葛韦格的成人玩具故事非常有趣</a></strong></li></ul><p>据<a href="https://www.gamesradar.com/oceans-11-prequel-margot-robbie-ryan-gosling-saltburn/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Games Radar</em></a>报道，两人将合作制作<em>《十一</em>罗汉》前传，由罗比的制作公司 LuckyChap Entertainment 执导。</p><p>关于该项目的细节知之甚少，但它是由杰伊·罗奇执导的，他也执导过<em>《王牌大贱谍》</em> 。据说故事背景是20世纪60年代的欧洲。</p><p> Producer Josey McNamara opened up a little more about the project at the BFI London film festival to <em>Games Radar</em> , saying: “I can&#39;t really say much…but I think we&#39;re just trying to do right by the franchise. I&#39;m excited for people to experience it when it&#39;s ready.”</p><p> Speaking about the reunion of Robbie and Gosling, McNamara added: “They&#39;re wonderful together. The more projects even outside of that we can have them do would be amazing.” </p><figure id="attachment_3355990" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3355990" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3355990" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie-.jpg" alt="Margot Robbie Stars as 'Barbie'" width="2000" height="1275" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie-.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie--400x255.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie--800x510.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie--696x444.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie--1392x887.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/Margot-Robbie-is-Barbie--1068x681.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3355990" class="wp-caption-text"> Margot Robbie in &#39;Barbie&#39;. CREDIT: Warner Bros</figcaption></figure><p> Earlier this week, legendary director <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/martin-scorsese">Martin Scorsese</a> said the simultaneous release of <em>Barbie</em> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/films/oppenheimer"><em>Oppenheimer</em></a> was <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/martin-scorsese-says-barbenheimer-was-something-special-3512485">a “wonderful” thing for cinema this summer.</a></p><p> The director discussed the “Barbenheimer” phenomena during an interview with the <a href="https://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/hollywood/martin-scorsese-interview-killers-of-the-flower-moon-leonardo-dicaprio-robert-de-niro-apple-tv-101695989444345.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>Hindustan Times</em></a> , saying that it offered “hope” for a different kind of film landscape.</p><p> “I do think that combination of <em>Oppenheimer</em> and <em>Barbie</em> was something special,” Scorsese said. “It seemed to be, I hate that word, but the perfect storm. It came about at the right time. And the most important thing is that people went to watch these in a theatre. And I think that&#39;s wonderful.”</p><p> While the director admitted he hasn&#39;t seen either film yet, he explained that he&#39;s a fan of both <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/christopher-nolan">Christopher Nolan</a> and Robbie – who had her breakthrough role in Scorsese&#39;s 2013 film <em>The Wolf Of Wall Street</em> .</p><p> “The way it fit perfectly – a film with such entertainment value, purely with the bright colours, and a film with such severity and strength, and pretty much about the danger of the end to our civilisation – you couldn&#39;t have more opposite films to work together.</p><p> “It does offer some hope for a different cinema to emerge, different from what&#39;s been happening in the last 20 years, aside from the great work being done in independent cinema,” he added.</p><p> <em>Barbie</em> has become the highest-grossing movie of the year worldwide so far, and the highest-grossing film ever by a female director.</p><p> In a<a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/film-reviews/barbie-review-margot-robbie-ryan-gosling-3470019">four-star review</a> , <em>NME</em> wrote: “What follows is a nuanced, rose-tinted comedy adventure, set to a stonking pop soundtrack featuring <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/lizzo">Lizzo</a> and <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/billie-eilish">Billie Eilish</a> , that somehow lives up to the immense hype. To borrow a pun from Ken&#39;s coolest jacket (out of a long lineup), <em>Barbie</em> is more than &#39;kenough&#39;.”</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/film/margot-robbie-and-ryan-gosling-are-reuniting-for-a-new-film-3513283">Margot Robbie and Ryan Gosling are reuniting for a new film</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
